examples.en: He swallowed his words
He swallowed the grape whole.
I swallowed the insult.
My dog swallowed a Lego part.
He swallowed some type of poison.
Robyn swallowed painfully.
The frog swallowed the fly whole.
Half of my salary is swallowed up by rent.
The snake swallowed its prey whole.
I swallowed my pride and phoned him.
She swallowed back a tide of emotion.
The building was swallowed up by flames
The dukedoms were swallowed up in kingdoms.
She swallowed the whole spoonful at one gulp.
He had swallowed so much sea water he wanted to vomit.
Small companies are swallowed up by huge multinationals.
He popped a piece of meat in(to) his mouth and swallowed greedily.
She was swallowed up in the crowd.
He swallowed a fishbone and gagged.
I swallowed my anger and kept quiet.
Leo swallowed hard and walked into the room.
She swallowed her anger and turned to face him.
The boss said, Come in. I swallowed hard and walked in.
